line_1: Thou art the life o' public haunts;
line_2: But thee, what were our fairs and rants?

line_1: Thou art the life o' public haunts;

line_1: A frantick Gipsey, now the House He haunts,
line_2: And in wild Phrases, speaks dissembled Wants.

line_1: Ah lead me, Genius, to thy haunts,
Choose on thy willow'd shore her lonely haunts!
line_2: Where o'er the rocks the mantling bindwith flaunts,
